      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameter distributions for boundary conditions and material properties must be defined and propagated through the model; confidence intervals on RH must be reported.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 500 samples. Input distributions defined for inlet flow rate (±3% CV), blood viscosity (±8% CV based on literature), and impeller tip clearance (±0.05 mm manufacturing tolerance). 95% confidence interval on RH index reported as [0.71, 0.94], remaining below the RH < 1 threshold. Dominant drivers are noted qualitatively in the UQ report narrative; a formal ranked sensitivity analysis is planned for a subsequent study but has not been completed for this submission."
